Certainly! Below is a Java program that downloads an image from a URL, applies a simple filter (e.g., a Gaussian blur), and saves the modified image to disk.

This program uses the `java.net` package to download the image, the `javax.imageio` package to read and write images, and the `java.awt.image` package for image processing (e.g., applying a Gaussian blur).

```java
import java.awt.image.BufferedImage;
import java.awt.image.GaussianBlur;
import java.io.*;
import java.net.URL;

public class ImageFilterDownloader {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String imageUrl = "https://example.com/sample-image.jpg"; // Replace with your image URL
        String outputFilePath = "filtered_image.jpg";

        try {
            BufferedImage originalImage = downloadImageFromUrl(imageUrl);
            BufferedImage filteredImage = applyFilter(originalImage);
            saveImageToFile(filteredImage, outputFilePath);
            System.out.println("Image saved to: " + outputFilePath);
        } catch (Exception e) {
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }

    private static BufferedImage downloadImageFromUrl(String imageUrl) throws IOException {
        URL url = new URL(imageUrl);
        BufferedImage image = ImageIO.read(url.openStream());
        return image;
    }

    private static BufferedImage applyFilter(BufferedImage image) {
        // Create a Gaussian blur filter
        GaussianBlur blur = new GaussianBlur(5, 5);
        BufferedImage filtered = new BufferedImage(image.getWidth(), image.getHeight(), image.getType());
        Graphics2D g2d = filtered.createGraphics();
        blur.filter(image, filtered);
        g2d.dispose();
        return filtered;
    }

    private static void saveImageToFile(BufferedImage image, String outputPath) throws IOException {
        ImageIO.write(image, "jpg", new File(outputPath));
    }
}
```

### Explanation:

- **`downloadImageFromUrl`**: Downloads an image from the specified URL and returns it as a `BufferedImage`.
- **`applyFilter`**: Applies a Gaussian blur filter to the image. You can modify this to apply other filters (e.g., brightness, contrast, etc.).
- **`saveImageToFile`**: Saves the filtered image to the specified file path in JPEG format.

### Notes:

- Ensure that the URL is valid and accessible.
- The `GaussianBlur` class is from the `java.awt.image` package, and it is used to simulate a blur effect.
